#Iron: 2.5Gt
hematite, magnetite
production: Australia (1Gt, Western), Brazil (0.5Gt, Minas Gerais + Pará), China, India, Russia (Kursk), South Africa, Canada, USA (Minnesota)

#Aluminium
bauxite: 450Mt, 15% aluminium yield (energy intensive)
production: Guinea (100Mt), Australia (100Mt), China, Brazil (Pará), India
aluminium (70Mt): China (40Mt), India, Russia, Canada, UAE

#Chromium: 45Mt, chromite
production: South Africa (20Mt), Turkey, Kazakhstan, India (Odisha)

#Copper: 20Mt, ofter silver and gold as byproducts
chalcopyrite, chalcocite
production: Chile (6Mt, Escondida), Peru, DRC (Kamoa-Kakula), China, USA (Arizona), Indonesia (Papua, Grasberg), Russia, Australia

#Manganese: 20Mt
production: South Africa (6Mt), China, Australia, Gabon

#Zinc: 13Mt
production: China (4Mt), Peru, Australia

#Titanium: 10Mt
ilmenite
production: China (3.5Mt), Mozambique, South Africa, Australia

#Nickel: 3Mt
production: Indonesia (800kt), Philippines, Russia

#Tin: 300kt
cassiterite
production: China (85kt), Indonesia (Bangka + Belitung), Myanmar

#Cobalt: 200kt
production: DR Congo (130kt, Tenke Fungurume)

#Lithium: 130kt
production: Australia (60kt), Chile, China

#Uranium: 50kt
production: Kazakhstan (20kt), Namibia, Canada, Australia
reserves: Australia, Kazakhstan, Canada, Russia

#Silver: 25kt
production: Mexico (6kt), China, Peru, Chile
historical production: Poland (Tarnowskie Góry, Katowice), Austria (Schwaz, Tirol), Germany (Freiberg, Saxony)

#Gold: 3kt
production: China (300t), Australia (Western), Russia (Siberia), Canada, USA (Nevada, Alaska, California), Ghana, Indonesia (Papua, Grasberg)
historical production: South Africa (1kt, Witwatersrand Basin, Johannesburg)
reserves: Australia, Russia, South Africa, USA, Peru, Indonesia, Brazil, Canada

#Platinum (PGM): 200t
production: South Africa (120t), Russia, Zimbabwe

#Rare-earth element (REE): lanthanides
production: China, Australia
reserves: Brazil, Vietnam

#Mineral resource: concentration of material of reasonable quality+quantity
Inferred: estimated with low confidence,
Indicated: estimated with medium confidence
Measured: estimated with high confidence

#Mineral reserve: economically mineable mineral resource
Probable: indicated mineral resource
Proved: measured mineral resource

Acid mine drainage: outflow of acidic water due to oxidation of sulfide minerals (Witwatersrand, Rio Tinto)
Heavy mineral sands: zircon + ilmenite + rutile accumulated on coastlines
Porphyry copper deposits: massive, formed from hydrothermal fluids, open pits, largest copper source, molybdenum by-product

#Lapidary: shaping minerals into decorative items
Cabochon: polished opaque gemstone, rounded obverse and flat reverse
Facets: flat faces on transparent gemstone
Intaglio: engraved gemstone, into background
Cameo: carved gemstone, out of background (onyx)
